-- HKEx shares surge 9 pct on new cross-border investment rules
-- By Lawrence White
-- Thu Apr 10, 2014 09:43PM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, April 11 (Reuters) - Hong Kong Exchanges and Clearing <0388.HK> shares rose 9 percent on Friday, as investors welcomed China's announcement that it would allow cross-border share trading between Hong Kong and Shanghai. [ID:nL3N0N21SK]

HKEx shares were suspended on Thursday pending an announcement. China's securities regulator said it would allow mainland investors to trade shares in designated companies listed in Hong Kong, and at the same time let Hong Kong investors buy shares in Shanghai-listed firms.